verses.text_plain: The word that the Lord spake against Babylon and against the land of the Chaldeans by Jeremiah the prophet.
verses.verse_html:
1The word that the Lord spake against Babylon and against the land of the Chaldeans by Jeremiah the prophet. ▼
▼ by…: Heb. by the hand of Jeremiah

footnotes.body_text: ▼ by…: Heb. by the hand of Jeremiah
footnotes.body_html: ▼ by…: Heb. by the hand of Jeremiah

verses.text_plain: Declare ye among the nations, and publish, and set up a standard; publish, and conceal not: say, Babylon is taken, Bel is confounded, Merodach is broken in pieces; her idols are confounded, her images are broken in pieces.
verses.verse_html:
2Declare ye among the nations, and publish, and set up a standard; publish, and conceal not: say, Babylon is taken, Bel is confounded, Merodach is broken in pieces; her idols are confounded, her images are broken in pieces. ▼
▼ set up: Heb. lift up

footnotes.body_html: ▼ set up: Heb. lift up

verses.text_plain: For out of the north there cometh up a nation against her, which shall make her land desolate, and none shall dwell therein: they shall remove, they shall depart, both man and beast.
verses.verse_html: 3For out of the north there cometh up a nation against her, which shall make her land desolate, and none shall dwell therein: they shall remove, they shall depart, both man and beast.

verses.text_plain: In those days, and in that time, saith the Lord, the children of Israel shall come, they and the children of Judah together, going and weeping: they shall go, and seek the Lord their God.
verses.verse_html: 4In those days, and in that time, saith the Lord, the children of Israel shall come, they and the children of Judah together, going and weeping: they shall go, and seek the Lord their God.

verses.text_plain: They shall ask the way to Zion with their faces thitherward, saying, Come, and let us join ourselves to the Lord in a perpetual covenant that shall not be forgotten.
verses.verse_html: 5They shall ask the way to Zion with their faces thitherward, saying, Come, and let us join ourselves to the Lord in a perpetual covenant that shall not be forgotten.

verses.text_plain: My people hath been lost sheep: their shepherds have caused them to go astray, they have turned them away on the mountains: they have gone from mountain to hill, they have forgotten their restingplace.
verses.verse_html:
6My people hath been lost sheep: their shepherds have caused them to go astray, they have turned them away on the mountains: they have gone from mountain to hill, they have forgotten their restingplace. ▼
▼ restingplace: Heb. place to lie down in

tokens.text: have caused them to go astray

footnotes.body_text: ▼ restingplace: Heb. place to lie down in
footnotes.body_html: ▼ restingplace: Heb. place to lie down in

verses.text_plain: All that found them have devoured them: and their adversaries said, We offend not, because they have sinned against the Lord, the habitation of justice, even the Lord, the hope of their fathers.
verses.verse_html: 7All that found them have devoured them: and their adversaries said, We offend not, because they have sinned against the Lord, the habitation of justice, even the Lord, the hope of their fathers.

verses.text_plain: Remove out of the midst of Babylon, and go forth out of the land of the Chaldeans, and be as the he goats before the flocks.
verses.verse_html: 8Remove out of the midst of Babylon, and go forth out of the land of the Chaldeans, and be as the he goats before the flocks.

tokens.text: and be as the he goats

verses.text_plain: For, lo, I will raise and cause to come up against Babylon an assembly of great nations from the north country: and they shall set themselves in array against her; from thence she shall be taken: their arrows shall be as of a mighty expert man; none shall return in vain.
verses.verse_html:
9For, lo, I will raise and cause to come up against Babylon an assembly of great nations from the north country: and they shall set themselves in array against her; from thence she shall be taken: their arrows shall be as of a mighty expert man; none shall return in vain. ▼
▼ expert…: or, destroyer

tokens.text: and they shall set themselves in array
against her; from thence she shall be taken

verses.text_plain: And Chaldea shall be a spoil: all that spoil her shall be satisfied, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 10And Chaldea shall be a spoil: all that spoil her shall be satisfied, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Because ye were glad, because ye rejoiced, O ye destroyers of mine heritage, because ye are grown fat as the heifer at grass, and bellow as bulls;
verses.verse_html:
11Because ye were glad, because ye rejoiced, O ye destroyers of mine heritage, because ye are grown fat as the heifer at grass, and bellow as bulls; ▼
▼ fat: Heb. big, or, corpulent
 , ▼
▼ bellow…: or, neigh as steeds

footnotes.body_html: ▼ fat: Heb. big, or, corpulent
▼ bellow…: or, neigh as steeds

verses.text_plain: Your mother shall be sore confounded; she that bare you shall be ashamed: behold, the hindermost of the nations shall be a wilderness, a dry land, and a desert.
verses.verse_html: 12Your mother shall be sore confounded; she that bare you shall be ashamed: behold, the hindermost of the nations shall be a wilderness, a dry land, and a desert.

verses.text_plain: Because of the wrath of the Lord it shall not be inhabited, but it shall be wholly desolate: every one that goeth by Babylon shall be astonished, and hiss at all her plagues.
verses.verse_html: 13Because of the wrath of the Lord it shall not be inhabited, but it shall be wholly desolate: every one that goeth by Babylon shall be astonished, and hiss at all her plagues.

tokens.text: but it shall be wholly desolate

verses.text_plain: Put yourselves in array against Babylon round about: all ye that bend the bow, shoot at her, spare no arrows: for she hath sinned against the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 14Put yourselves in array against Babylon round about: all ye that bend the bow, shoot at her, spare no arrows: for she hath sinned against the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Shout against her round about: she hath given her hand: her foundations are fallen, her walls are thrown down: for it is the vengeance of the Lord: take vengeance upon her; as she hath done, do unto her.
verses.verse_html: 15Shout against her round about: she hath given her hand: her foundations are fallen, her walls are thrown down: for it is the vengeance of the Lord: take vengeance upon her; as she hath done, do unto her.

tokens.text: upon her; as she hath done

verses.text_plain: Cut off the sower from Babylon, and him that handleth the sickle in the time of harvest: for fear of the oppressing sword they shall turn every one to his people, and they shall flee every one to his own land.
verses.verse_html:
16Cut off the sower from Babylon, and him that handleth the sickle in the time of harvest: for fear of the oppressing sword they shall turn every one to his people, and they shall flee every one to his own land. ▼
▼ sickle: or, scythe

verses.text_plain: Israel is a scattered sheep; the lions have driven him away: first the king of Assyria hath devoured him; and last this Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon hath broken his bones.
verses.verse_html: 17Israel is a scattered sheep; the lions have driven him away: first the king of Assyria hath devoured him; and last this Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon hath broken his bones.

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel; Behold, I will punish the king of Babylon and his land, as I have punished the king of Assyria.
verses.verse_html: 18Therefore thus saith the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel; Behold, I will punish the king of Babylon and his land, as I have punished the king of Assyria.

verses.text_plain: And I will bring Israel again to his habitation, and he shall feed on Carmel and Bashan, and his soul shall be satisfied upon mount Ephraim and Gilead.
verses.verse_html: 19And I will bring Israel again to his habitation, and he shall feed on Carmel and Bashan, and his soul shall be satisfied upon mount Ephraim and Gilead.

verses.text_plain: In those days, and in that time, saith the Lord, the iniquity of Israel shall be sought for, and there shall be none; and the sins of Judah, and they shall not be found: for I will pardon them whom I reserve.
verses.verse_html: 20In those days, and in that time, saith the Lord, the iniquity of Israel shall be sought for, and there shall be none; and the sins of Judah, and they shall not be found: for I will pardon them whom I reserve.

tokens.text: and they shall not be found

verses.text_plain: Go up against the land of Merathaim, even against it, and against the inhabitants of Pekod: waste and utterly destroy after them, saith the Lord, and do according to all that I have commanded thee.
verses.verse_html:
21Go up against the land of Merathaim, even against it, and against the inhabitants of Pekod: waste and utterly destroy after them, saith the Lord, and do according to all that I have commanded thee. ▼
▼ of Merathaim: or, of the rebels
 , ▼
▼ Pekod: or, Visitation

tokens.text: against it, and against the inhabitants
according to all that I have commanded

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of Merathaim: or, of the rebels
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of Merathaim: or, of the rebels

verses.text_plain: A sound of battle is in the land, and of great destruction.
verses.verse_html: 22A sound of battle is in the land, and of great destruction.

verses.text_plain: How is the hammer of the whole earth cut asunder and broken! how is Babylon become a desolation among the nations!
verses.verse_html: 23How is the hammer of the whole earth cut asunder and broken! how is Babylon become a desolation among the nations!

verses.text_plain: I have laid a snare for thee, and thou art also taken, O Babylon, and thou wast not aware: thou art found, and also caught, because thou hast striven against the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 24I have laid a snare for thee, and thou art also taken, O Babylon, and thou wast not aware: thou art found, and also caught, because thou hast striven against the Lord.

tokens.text: for thee, and thou art also taken

verses.text_plain: The Lord hath opened his armoury, and hath brought forth the weapons of his indignation: for this is the work of the Lord God of hosts in the land of the Chaldeans.
verses.verse_html: 25The Lord hath opened his armoury, and hath brought forth the weapons of his indignation: for this is the work of the Lord God of hosts in the land of the Chaldeans.

verses.text_plain: Come against her from the utmost border, open her storehouses: cast her up as heaps, and destroy her utterly: let nothing of her be left.
verses.verse_html:
26Come against her from the utmost border, open her storehouses: cast her up as heaps, and destroy her utterly: let nothing of her be left. ▼
▼ from…: Heb. from the end
 , ▼
▼ cast…: or, tread her

tokens.text: against her from the utmost border
let nothing of her be left

footnotes.body_html: ▼ from…: Heb. from the end
▼ cast…: or, tread her

verses.text_plain: Slay all her bullocks; let them go down to the slaughter: woe unto them! for their day is come, the time of their visitation.
verses.verse_html: 27Slay all her bullocks; let them go down to the slaughter: woe unto them! for their day is come, the time of their visitation.

verses.text_plain: The voice of them that flee and escape out of the land of Babylon, to declare in Zion the vengeance of the Lord our God, the vengeance of his temple.
verses.verse_html: 28The voice of them that flee and escape out of the land of Babylon, to declare in Zion the vengeance of the Lord our God, the vengeance of his temple.

verses.text_plain: Call together the archers against Babylon: all ye that bend the bow, camp against it round about; let none thereof escape: recompense her according to her work; according to all that she hath done, do unto her: for she hath been proud against the Lord, against the Holy One of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 29Call together the archers against Babylon: all ye that bend the bow, camp against it round about; let none thereof escape: recompense her according to her work; according to all that she hath done, do unto her: for she hath been proud against the Lord, against the Holy One of Israel.

tokens.text: according to all that she hath done
unto her: for she hath been proud

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall her young men fall in the streets, and all her men of war shall be cut off in that day, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 30Therefore shall her young men fall in the streets, and all her men of war shall be cut off in that day, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Behold, I am against thee, O thou most proud, saith the Lord God of hosts: for thy day is come, the time that I will visit thee.
verses.verse_html:
31Behold, I am against thee, O thou most proud, saith the Lord God of hosts: for thy day is come, the time that I will visit thee. ▼
▼ most…: Heb. pride

verses.text_plain: And the most proud shall stumble and fall, and none shall raise him up: and I will kindle a fire in his cities, and it shall devour all round about him.
verses.verse_html:
32And the most proud shall stumble and fall, and none shall raise him up: and I will kindle a fire in his cities, and it shall devour all round about him. ▼
▼ the…: Heb. pride

tokens.text: and none shall raise him up

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord of hosts; The children of Israel and the children of Judah were oppressed together: and all that took them captives held them fast; they refused to let them go.
verses.verse_html: 33Thus saith the Lord of hosts; The children of Israel and the children of Judah were oppressed together: and all that took them captives held them fast; they refused to let them go.

tokens.text: and all that took them captives

verses.text_plain: Their Redeemer is strong; the Lord of hosts is his name: he shall throughly plead their cause, that he may give rest to the land, and disquiet the inhabitants of Babylon.
verses.verse_html: 34Their Redeemer is strong; the Lord of hosts is his name: he shall throughly plead their cause, that he may give rest to the land, and disquiet the inhabitants of Babylon.

verses.text_plain: A sword is upon the Chaldeans, saith the Lord, and upon the inhabitants of Babylon, and upon her princes, and upon her wise men.
verses.verse_html: 35A sword is upon the Chaldeans, saith the Lord, and upon the inhabitants of Babylon, and upon her princes, and upon her wise men.

verses.text_plain: A sword is upon the liars; and they shall dote: a sword is upon her mighty men; and they shall be dismayed.
verses.verse_html:
36A sword is upon the liars; and they shall dote: a sword is upon her mighty men; and they shall be dismayed. ▼
▼ liars: or, chief stays: Heb. bars

footnotes.body_text: ▼ liars: or, chief stays: Heb. bars
footnotes.body_html: ▼ liars: or, chief stays: Heb. bars

verses.text_plain: A sword is upon their horses, and upon their chariots, and upon all the mingled people that are in the midst of her; and they shall become as women: a sword is upon her treasures; and they shall be robbed.
verses.verse_html: 37A sword is upon their horses, and upon their chariots, and upon all the mingled people that are in the midst of her; and they shall become as women: a sword is upon her treasures; and they shall be robbed.

tokens.text: and upon all the mingled people
of her; and they shall become as women

verses.text_plain: A drought is upon her waters; and they shall be dried up: for it is the land of graven images, and they are mad upon their idols.
verses.verse_html: 38A drought is upon her waters; and they shall be dried up: for it is the land of graven images, and they are mad upon their idols.

tokens.text: and they shall be dried up

verses.text_plain: Therefore the wild beasts of the desert with the wild beasts of the islands shall dwell there, and the owls shall dwell therein: and it shall be no more inhabited for ever; neither shall it be dwelt in from generation to generation.
verses.verse_html: 39Therefore the wild beasts of the desert with the wild beasts of the islands shall dwell there, and the owls shall dwell therein: and it shall be no more inhabited for ever; neither shall it be dwelt in from generation to generation.

tokens.text: Therefore the wild beasts of the desert
with the wild beasts of the islands
therein: and it shall be no more inhabited

verses.text_plain: As God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah and the neighbour cities thereof, saith the Lord; so shall no man abide there, neither shall any son of man dwell therein.
verses.verse_html: 40As God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah and the neighbour cities thereof, saith the Lord; so shall no man abide there, neither shall any son of man dwell therein.

verses.text_plain: Behold, a people shall come from the north, and a great nation, and many kings shall be raised up from the coasts of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 41Behold, a people shall come from the north, and a great nation, and many kings shall be raised up from the coasts of the earth.

verses.text_plain: They shall hold the bow and the lance: they are cruel, and will not shew mercy: their voice shall roar like the sea, and they shall ride upon horses, every one put in array, like a man to the battle, against thee, O daughter of Babylon.
verses.verse_html: 42They shall hold the bow and the lance: they are cruel, and will not shew mercy: their voice shall roar like the sea, and they shall ride upon horses, every one put in array, like a man to the battle, against thee, O daughter of Babylon.

verses.text_plain: The king of Babylon hath heard the report of them, and his hands waxed feeble: anguish took hold of him, and pangs as of a woman in travail.
verses.verse_html: 43The king of Babylon hath heard the report of them, and his hands waxed feeble: anguish took hold of him, and pangs as of a woman in travail.

tokens.text: as of a woman in travail

verses.text_plain: Behold, he shall come up like a lion from the swelling of Jordan unto the habitation of the strong: but I will make them suddenly run away from her: and who is a chosen man, that I may appoint over her? for who is like me? and who will appoint me the time? and who is that shepherd that will stand before me?
verses.verse_html:
44Behold, he shall come up like a lion from the swelling of Jordan unto the habitation of the strong: but I will make them suddenly run away from her: and who is a chosen man, that I may appoint over her? for who is like me? and who will appoint me the time? and who is that shepherd that will stand before me? ▼
▼ appoint me…: or, convent me to plead?

tokens.text: like me? and who will appoint me the time

footnotes.body_text: ▼ appoint me…: or, convent me to plead?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ appoint me…: or, convent me to plead?

verses.text_plain: Therefore hear ye the counsel of the Lord, that he hath taken against Babylon; and his purposes, that he hath purposed against the land of the Chaldeans: Surely the least of the flock shall draw them out: surely he shall make their habitation desolate with them.
verses.verse_html: 45Therefore hear ye the counsel of the Lord, that he hath taken against Babylon; and his purposes, that he hath purposed against the land of the Chaldeans: Surely the least of the flock shall draw them out: surely he shall make their habitation desolate with them.

verses.text_plain: At the noise of the taking of Babylon the earth is moved, and the cry is heard among the nations.
verses.verse_html: 46At the noise of the taking of Babylon the earth is moved, and the cry is heard among the nations.
